n commit on branch B\n```\n\nThen PR trail admission becomes:\n\n```text\ninclude strongly if review target exists\nand either:\n  target appeared after targetless turns\n  or derived file-promotion ties prior work to this branch\n  or explicit mutating command names the target\n```\n\nSo yes: refine this. I’d call it **worktree-to-commit promotion detection**. It’s a much better heuristic than “mutating command occurred somewhere in the session,” and it avoids spreading agentlog concerns into GitButler mutation paths.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-26T12:44:41.334Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}